Material Information Summary

  • Drilling Commencement: Maiden diamond drilling started at La Florida copper prospect (Fortuna Project, Chile).
  • Program Details:
  • Initial 4-hole program (1,400m total) targeting newly defined copper zones.
  • Surface sampling previously returned up to 3.96% Cu and 2.61g/t Au.
  • Targets exhibit alteration/geochemical zonation indicative of copper mineralization.
  • Funding: Fully funded via A$3M equity raise completed May 2025.
  • Pending Results: Assays from trenching program still outstanding.
  • Strategic Context: Targets align with near-surface, infrastructure-proximal exploration strategy.

No material financial, capital structure, or liquidity impacts identified in this announcement.

Material Information Summary

Exploration Results Confirming High-Grade Gold Assays

  • Sampling Program Validation:
  • Confirms consistency of high-grade gold mineralisation from historic drill core and pulps.
  • Strong correlation between original and new assays supports robustness of past exploration data.

  • Key assay method for future drilling: 50g fire assay (FA50) and HQ drill core for representative sampling.

  • Standout Intercepts (Notable drill results from Lincoln-Comet and Medean prospects):

  • 8.9m @ 6.7 g/t Au (ddh-0203)
  • 1.8m @ 9.6 g/t Au (ddh-0164)
  • 6.7m @ 11.6 g/t Au (ddh-0165)
  • 13.3m @ 8.6 g/t Au (ddh-0195)

  • 1.2m @ 108.0 g/t Au (ddh-0198, highest single intercept)

  • Coarse Gold Confirmation:

  • High-grade intervals remain consistent despite variability due to coarse gold nature.

  • Individual ultra-high-grade samples:

    • 0.91m @ 59.4 g/t Au (ddh-0165)
    • 0.98m @ >100 g/t Au (ddh-0195)
    • 0.91m @ 304.5 g/t Au (ddh-0195)

  • Grade Distribution:

  • 66% of samples > 1.5 g/t Au, 37% > 3.5 g/t Au, 21% > 7.0 g/t Au.
  • Reinforces high-grade tenor of the mineralised system.

Next Steps

  • Final acquisition settlement expected this week.
  • Phase 1 drill program (2,000–2,500m HQ diamond drilling) set for August 2025, pending mine dewatering and infrastructure checks.

Key Takeaways for Traders/Investors

  • Validation of historic high-grade gold assays supports confidence in the deposit.
  • Upcoming drill program (FA50/HQ core) aims to improve resource estimation accuracy.
  • No capital raising or material corporate changes – focus remains on technical due diligence.

No material operational or financial metrics (cash balance, capex, etc.) disclosed.

Material Information Summary – Anson Resources (ASX: ASN)

  • Strategic Land Expansion:
  • Added 100 placer claims (+8.23km², 10% increase) at the Green River Lithium Project (Utah, USA).

  • 28% of new claims fall within the Area of Influence (AOI) and will be included in future JORC Resource upgrades.

  • Key Geological Highlights:

  • Two historical oil wells (Grand Fault Unit 14-24 and Green River Unit 1) on new claims recorded near-surface brine flows, indicating high porosity/permeability.
  • Grand Fault well is adjacent to a continuously flowing geyser, reinforcing reservoir potential.

  • No lithium assays from historic wells, but proximity to confirmed lithium-rich brine wells (e.g., Boysdaba #1) supports exploration upside.

  • Resource Potential:

  • Thick Mississippian Unit (672 feet) suggests broad brine reservoir.
  • Claims abut a recently granted State OBA lease, creating a contiguous 88.61km² area.

No material financial/timetable data identified.

Material Information Summary

Financial Performance (6 months to 31 Dec 2024)

  • Revenue: $7.8M (+100% YoY)
  • Loss before tax: $23.0M (+506% YoY)
  • Loss per share (basic/diluted): 2.3 cents (+472% YoY)
  • Cash balance: $1.0M (up from $0.8M at 30 Jun 2024)
  • Net tangible assets: Nil per share (unchanged).

Operational Highlights

  • Dolphin Tungsten Project:
  • Production: 257kt ore mined; 79kt processed (avg. grade 0.75%, recovery 44%).
  • Concentrate shipped: 433t (avg. grade 58%).
  • Operational challenges: Plant breakdowns, workforce shortages.
  • Tungsten market: APT price $300–$325/mtu (Rotterdam CIF).

Capital Structure & Debt Recapitalization

  • Debt conversion (completed 30 Apr 2025):
  • $81.1M debt + interest converted to equity via 19.2B new shares.
  • $5.9M equity raised via 1.7B shares ($0.0035/share).
  • 7.2B warrants issued (exercise price $0.0035, expiry Oct 2025).
  • New loans:
  • $17.8M facility from Senior Lending Group ($14.0M drawn by 31 Dec 2024).
  • $7.5M from Tasmanian Government (fully drawn May 2025, maturity Apr 2027).
  • Post-recapitalization proforma: Net debt reduced to $33.2M (mostly due Apr 2027).

Subsequent Events

  • Options/warrants:
  • 76M options issued to Executive Chairman (Kevin Pallas).
  • Multiple options expired/lapsed (e.g., 21.1M G6MAK @ $0.28).
  • R&D tax refund: $2.1M received June 2025.

Liquidity & Going Concern

  • Material uncertainty: Relies on operational turnaround (plant optimization, cost cuts) to avoid covenant breaches.
  • Cash forecast assumptions:
  • Target processing rate: 24kt/month ore @ 0.7% grade, 60% recovery.
  • APT price: $347/mtu USD (AUD/USD 0.67).

Key Takeaways for Trading/Capital Markets

  1. High financial risk: Negative equity ($81.1M deficit), aggressive dilution (19.2B shares issued), and operational underperformance.
  2. Debt overhang addressed: Recapitalization reduces near-term liquidity pressure but leaves significant leverage.
  3. Execution dependency: Valuation hinges on operational stabilization and tungsten price strength.

No dividends declared.

Material Information Summary

Key Highlights (Exploration Results)

  • High-grade intercepts confirming resource continuity:
  • 22m @ 3.25g/t Au (Bacchus, including 8m @ 7.5g/t)
  • 13m @ 4.1g/t Au (including 1m @ 23.4g/t)

  • Drilling progress:
  • 143 holes completed (30,367m) of planned 80,000m program (~40% complete).
  • Assays pending for 69 holes.
  • Resource expansion potential:
  • Depth extensions confirmed at Phoenix (930koz) and Bacchus (894koz) deposits.
  • Strike continuity established between Bacchus and Kraken deposits.
  • Upcoming catalyst: Updated Mineral Resource Estimate (MRE) expected in Q4 2025.

Operational & Exploration Updates

  • Heritage surveys: Completed, clearing access for further drilling.
  • Auger drilling: Commenced at Gibraltar prospect (untested lithological contacts).
  • Geophysics: Dipole-Dipole IP survey over Bacchus/Kraken (results pending).

JORC Compliance & Tenement Details

  • Resource base: 2.3Moz Au (60Mt @ 1.2g/t), 100%-owned (subject to royalties).
  • Royalties: 1% gross (Franco Nevada), A$10/oz (Vox Royalty) on specified tenements.

Conclusion: Results support resource growth potential, with high-grade hits reinforcing project viability. Focus remains on infill drilling and MRE update.
